INSURANCE DEPARTMENT. Requires the inclusion of the license number of adjusters,
appraisers, and contractors in all written communications. (8/1/26)
1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 22:1674.1(A)(22), 1706(H)(12), and 1807.16(D)(5) and R.S. 37:2156.1(K),
3 relative to requiring the inclusion of certain licensing numbers in written
4 communications; to regulate insurance adjusters, public adjusters, insurance
5 appraisers, and contractors; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. R.S. 22:1674.1(A)(22), 1706(H)(12), and 1807.16(D)(5) are hereby
8 enacted to read as follows:
9 §1674.1. Standards of conduct; acknowledgment required
10 A. The following standards of conduct shall be binding on all claims
11 adjusters:
12 * * *
13 (22) An adjuster shall include his Louisiana license number in all written
14 communications, including electronic communications, composed and sent as
15 part of his business or employment.
